The tip of the feet towards the center
Weeks after suddenly becoming a widow, Cristina Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez, president of Argentina, has enjoyed a wave of public sympathy that has improved her approval rate by 20 points, to over 50%; it is her highest level since she was elected in 2007.
Yet turning this into a successful campaign for a second term in an election next year could depend on the choice of Ms. Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez, apparently in mourning, that she would abandon or not the intransigence of her late husband, predecessor and former political partner, Nestor Kirchner.
