The Russians believe, to an overwhelming majority, that their society is corrupt; according to polls.
But it is unusual to find the information in an embassy report; and it is unheard of to conceive that it would be up to diplomats from a foreign country to do so.
The direct link established between the Moscow city government and crime has led some people to call it “disfunctional” and claim that the government functioned more as a kleptocracy than a government, according to the embassy’s note.
“Criminal elements enjoy a ‘krysha’ (a term used in the criminal world/the mafia which literally means ‘roof’ or protection) that passes through the police, the Federal Security Service (FSB), the Ministry of the Interior (MVD) and the prosecutor’s office, as well as through the entire bureaucracy of the Moscow city government.
